text: Donna Taggart is a Celtic singer and musician. Born in Omagh in County Tyrone in Northern Ireland she first came to prominence in 2011 when her acclaimed debut album Celtic Lady Vol. 1 was picked up by highly respected BBC Radio Ulster presenter Gerry Anderson. Donna shot to fame in 2016 with over 27 million Facebook views of her video rendition of "Jealous of the Angels" which was written by Jenn Bostic in 2010. Jenn Bostic won five awards at the 2012 Independent Country Music Association, and the song reached number one on the UK iTunes Music charts. ==References== Category:Date of birth missing (living people) Category:Living people Category:Female singers from Northern Ireland Category:People from Omagh Category:Year of birth missing (living people) Category:Musicians from County Tyrone
